## The Leonardo DiCaprio Toast Meme

The Great Gatsby Reaction or Leonardo DiCaprio Toast refers to a series of reaction images and GIFs featuring actor Leonardo DiCaprio as Jay Gatsby toasting a martini glass from the 2013 film The Great Gatsby.(no content)Typically the reaction is used to show agreement or praise for something, but it is also used as an image macro in memes.

## Viral Status and Longevity

The meme has shown remarkable staying power over the years. Ten years after the film's release, the GIF was still going strong.(no content)The translator of the 2023 French edition of Gatsby attributed the novel's popularity in the country in part to the ubiquity of Leo Toasting.

## Cultural Impact in 2023

In a 2023 Reddit poll, users knew the meme, but a majority couldn't correctly identify the film where it came from. This demonstrates how the meme has transcended its source material to become a standalone cultural phenomenon.

## Origins and Usage

According to the website Know Your Meme, the Toast as a meme was born in the cradle of all things genuinely cool, the blogging website Tumblr. It appeared initially as a reaction image to American singer Fergie's song, "A Little Party Never Killed Nobody (All We Got)".(no content)The bulk of the memes, however, were made as reactions in praise of something.(no content)In short, you don't need to know The Great Gatsby; you just need to vibe with DiCaprio holding a martini.

The meme's enduring popularity speaks to its versatility and the universal appeal of DiCaprio's charismatic toast, making it one of the most recognizable movie memes on the internet.
